.TH "snd_hdac_get_connections" 9 "snd_hdac_get_connections" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hdac_get_connections \- get a widget connection list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_hdac_get_connections
.BI "(struct hdac_device *codec "  ","
.BI "hda_nid_t nid "  ","
.BI "hda_nid_t *conn_list "  ","
.BI "int max_conns "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "codec" 12
the codec object
.IP "nid" 12
NID
.IP "conn_list" 12
the array to store the results, can be NULL
.IP "max_conns" 12
the max size of the given array
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the number of connected widgets, zero for no connection, or a
negative error code.  When the number of elements don't fit with the
given array size, it returns -ENOSPC.

When \fIconn_list\fP is NULL, it just checks the number of connections.
